(249, 18, 'Use Rocket Jump to leap over an enemy and then use Buster Shot to send them flying back to your allies, but be careful about using this strategy in large team fights.'),
(250, 18, 'Using the active ability on Explosive Shot can be useful early game to prevent the other team from healing or using health potions.'),
(251, 48, 'Trundle excels at fighting within his Contaminate zone. Try to draw enemies onto it.'),
(252, 48, 'Use Agony to soften a powerful enemy tank or to create a target for your team to focus fire.'),
(253, 48, 'Rabid Bite is good for lowering the physical damage of enemies; try to focus it on enemy physical damage dealers.'),
(254, 23, 'Delaying the activation of Undying Rage is a very effective way to make an enemy champion over-commit to trying to kill you.'),
(255, 23, 'Bloodlust is an excellent way to heal Tryndamere. Try not to let it fade off before you activate it.'),
(256, 23, 'If the enemy is stacking Armor, try building items like Last Whisper or Youmuu\'s Ghostblade.'),
(257, 4, 'Coordinate with your allies for the best time to use Destiny to ambush enemies.'),
(258, 4, 'Stealth characters often escape a battle with very low hit points. Take advantage of Destiny\'s ability to reveal stealthed units to finish them off.'),
(259, 4, 'Twisted Fate is viable as an Attack Damage or Ability Power character, letting him fit on many different team compositions.'),
(260, 29, 'Twitch\'s attack speed is among the highest in the game; try purchasing items with on-hit effects such as Black Cleaver or Wit\'s End.'),
(261, 29, 'Expunge has a large range; apply as many stacks of Deadly Venom as possible before using it.'),
(262, 29, 'You can catch up to an enemy out of attack range with Venom Cask.'),
(263, 77, 'Damage is applied to turtle shield post-mitigation. Therefore, buying defensive items can drastically increase your survivability.'),
(264, 77, 'Udyr is one of the best junglers in the game. Taking advantage of this can give your team a large XP advantage and map control.'),
(265, 6, 'Prior to firing Acid Hunter, try hovering over an enemy afflicted by Noxian Corrosive Charge. Upon launching, the Acid Hunter will ignore all other enemies and fly directly to the corroding target.'),
(266, 6, 'Urgot is a great skirmisher. Try hitting his enemies with Noxian Corrosive Charge followed by multiple missile-locked Acid Hunters.'),
(267, 110, 'An early point in Blighted Quiver helps harass enemy champions and get killing blows on minions.'),
(268, 110, 'During short range fights it\'s sometimes best to fire Piercing Arrow quickly, rather than charging it to full power.'),
(269, 110, 'Try to take advantage of Piercing Arrow\'s very long range to snipe at enemy champions before a fight or as they\'re trying to flee.'),
(270, 67, 'Tumble has many uses, but it cannot pass over walls.'),
(271, 67, 'Condemn can be used to both pin targets to walls to ensure a kill, or to escape a pursuer.'),
(272, 67, 'Don\'t go in first to a large teamfight. Wait for your teammates to initiate.'),
(273, 45, 'Use Event Horizon to guarantee success landing Dark Matter.'),
(274, 45, 'Veigar is extremely mana-hungry early. Try buying mana regen items to increase the effectiveness of your passive and allow you to cast more Baleful Strikes.'),
(275, 45, 'Veigar is very fragile. It is valuable to select at least one summoner spell that can be used defensively.'),
(276, 254, 'A fully charged Vault Breaker will deal double damage.  It\'s great for catching and finishing off fleeing enemies.'),
(277, 254, 'Excessive Force does full damage to anyone caught in the shockwave.  Use it on minions in lane to hit enemies hiding behind them.'),
(278, 254, 'Assault and Battery is a powerful initiation tool, just remember not to get too far ahead of the rest of your team.'),
(279, 112, 'Death Ray is a powerful poke and a strong area of denial tool. Use it in combination with Graviton Field to control your enemy\'s position.'),
(280, 112, 'Make sure you choose the right augment. Each augment serves to boost specific strengths in Viktor and can only be purchased once a game.'),
(281, 8, 'Transfusion instantly deals damage to the enemy before healing Vladimir, making it one of the best last hitting tools in the game.'),
(282, 8, 'Cast Hemoplague where it will afflict the most units.'),
(283, 8, 'Sanguine Pool pops incoming missiles, so it can be used to dodge disables.'),
(284, 106, 'Lead the charge with Rolling Thunder and slow enemies with Majestic Roar.'),
(285, 106, 'Volibear benefits a great deal from additional health and cooldown reduction.'),
(286, 106, 'You must attack three times in rapid succession before Frenzy can be activated--having the toughness to survive for a long time is one way to accomplish this goal.'),
(287, 19, 'Warwick is a champion particularly well-suited for killing monsters in the forest. Hungering Strike can sustain your health, especially if you are able to get the Ancient Golem\'s blue buff.'),
(288, 19, 'Warwick\'s ultimate can stack on-hit effects such as the Black Cleaver or Wit\'s End.'),
(289, 62, 'Decoy and Nimbus Strike work well together to quickly strike your enemy and get out before they can retaliate.'),
(290, 62, 'Try using Decoy near brush to make an enemy overreact to your movement.'),
(291, 62, 'Oracle\'s Elixir will allow an opponent to see you even when using Decoy.'),
(292, 101, 'It\'s easier to land Arcanopulse on an enemy when they\'re moving toward or away from you, rather than side to side.'),
(293, 101, 'While casting Locus of Power you can begin lining up your next spell.'),
(294, 101, 'Rylai\'s Crystal Scepter will make landing Arcanopulse after Mage Chains easier as the target will be slowed.'),
(295, 5, 'Xin Zhao is a great initiator to combat. Lead the front to start a fight and use your ultimate to do the most damage possible.'),
(296, 5, 'It\'s often worth getting at least 1 point of Battle Cry to gain the health restore effect.'),
(297, 5, 'Try to position yourself so your ultimate\'s knockback is most effective'),
(298, 83, 'Omen of Pestilence can be used to block incoming skillshots.'),
(299, 83, 'Omen of Death can become more reliable if you cast it right before allies die, but it is less powerful.'),
(300, 83, 'During Omen of Death, both the Revenant and Reanimated champion count as a summon toward Unholy Covenant\'s bonus.'),
(301, 154, 'Picking up goo chunks is very important to staying alive.'),
(302, 154, 'When Cell Division is ready, try to die in a position that makes it difficult for the enemy team to kill your bloblets.'),
(303, 154, 'Charging Elastic Slingshot from the fog of war will give opponents less time to react.'),
(304, 238, 'Saving energy and spell cooldowns until you use your ultimate will maximize Death Mark\'s damage.'),
(305, 238, 'Quickly double tapping Living Shadow will teleport Zed to his shadow immediately for rapid escapes.'),
(306, 238, 'Placing a Living Shadow before using Death Mark can give Zed a safe escape from combat.'),
(307, 115, 'Even if you\'re far from a fight you can still help from afar with Mega Inferno Bomb.'),
(308, 115, 'Slowing your enemies with Hexplosive Minefield makes it easier to land other abilities.'),
(309, 115, 'Knocking yourself over walls with Satchel Charge can be great when chasing after or escaping from enemies.'),
(310, 26, 'You can combine the use of Time Bomb and Rewind to place two Time Bombs on a target quickly. Placing the second bomb will detonate the first.'),
(311, 26, 'Time Warp is an effective way to enable allies to finish off enemies, or escape from a losing battle.'),
(312, 26, 'Chronoshift is a powerful deterent to attacking your carries, but casting Chronoshift too early in a fight can cause the enemy to switch targets too soon, making it less effective.'),
(313, 143, 'Placing a seed in your spell\'s path after you have cast it gives you the best chance of having a seed in the proper spot.'),
(314, 143, 'Seeds grant vision to your team.'),
(315, 143, 'Zyra is a great ambusher -- Look for opportunities to set a trap of seeds in brush, then lure enemies in.');
